      <originalsloc id="aspace_ed24f8cce7031343ecfdb692ea49acd4">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection is available on microfilm (HM 200) and in the Winthrop-Weston Family Papers (MS 549).   The papers primarily contain the family correspondence of William Woolsey Winthrop (1831-1899), his sister Sarah Chauncey Winthrop Weston, and their mother, Elizabeth Dwight Woolsey Winthrop. Several letters were written by William Winthrop from St. Anthony, Minnesota and others concern his Civil War military experiences.</p>  
